<paragraph blockId="9.[365,1226,1788,1886]" box="[745,846,1859,1886]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<figureCitation box="[745,846,1859,1886]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionStartId-1="12.[189,232,1434,1460]" captionTargetBox-0="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetBox-1="[187,1400,267,1383]" captionTargetId-0="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetId-1="figure-174@12.[183,1406,259,1393]" captionTargetPageId-0="11" captionTargetPageId-1="12" captionText-0="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." captionText-1="Fig. 6. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862187" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6862187/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Figs 5–6</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[191,312,1917,1943]" box="[191,312,1917,1943]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<heading bold="true" box="[191,312,1917,1943]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[191,312,1917,1943]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[191,1401,1963,2026]" lastBlockId="10.[189,1398,265,327]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
The salient features of the new species include: centre of dorsal margin of periandrium with a short laminal process, base large, apex bifurcated (
<figureCitation box="[710,827,1999,2026]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Fig. 5J–L</figureCitation>
); ventrally around midlength of periandrium with a slender spinose process, slightly curved (
<figureCitation box="[700,801,265,292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5M</figureCitation>
); apical part of endosoma bifurcated, margin with small teeth (
<figureCitation box="[335,461,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5J–M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,324,373,399]" box="[189,324,373,399]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,373,399]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,373,399]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1398,420,481]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
The specific name is derived frOm the Latin adjective ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[830,925,420,446]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcutus">
<emphasis box="[830,925,420,446]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">furcutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, referring to the bifurcate apical part of the endosoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
