<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,334,826,852]" box="[189,334,826,852]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,826,852]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,826,852]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1190,872,899]" box="[189,1190,872,899]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
MEASUREMENTS. Body length: male 
<quantity box="[611,752,872,899]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.85" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="6.85" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="6.5">6.5–7.2 mm</quantity>
(N = 8), female 
<quantity box="[948,1089,873,899]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.45" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="7.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="7.45" valueMax="7.7" valueMin="7.2">7.2–7.7 mm</quantity>
(N = 4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[188,1399,945,1112]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
COLORATION. General color light brown (
<figureCitation box="[676,806,945,972]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5A–B</figureCitation>
). Eyes yellowish brown, ocelli faint yellow, semitranslucent. Antenna, vertex and face generally light brown. Rostrum brown. Pronotum and mesonotum brown. Forewing semi-translucent, with many small dark brown spots and irregular smoky speckle stripes. Stigma and veins yellowish brown. Tubercles blackish brown. Hind tibiae yellowish brown. Ventral abdomen yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,1159,1368]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
HEAD AND THORAX. Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[537,672,1159,1186]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5A, C</figureCitation>
) as long as wide; lateral carinae strongly elevated, median carina absent. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[449,543,1194,1221]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
) 3.6× as long as wide. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[969,1100,1194,1221]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5A, C</figureCitation>
) 1.4× as long as vertex; posterior margin forming an obtuse angle. Mesonotum 1.2× as long as pronotum and vertex combined. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[319,446,1265,1292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5B, E</figureCitation>
) 2.2 × as long as wide, with fourteen apical cells and seven subapical cells; RP with 5 branches; MP with 5 branches: MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[693,709,1319,1333]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">11</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[768,785,1319,1333]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">12</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[844,853,1319,1333]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">2</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[911,920,1319,1333]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">3</subScript>
and MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1022,1031,1319,1333]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">4</subScript>
; fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1148,1157,1319,1333]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">1</subScript>
+ MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1223,1232,1319,1333]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">2</subScript>
basad of fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[231,240,1354,1368]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">3</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[306,315,1354,1368]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">4</subScript>
. Metatibiotarsal formula 8/8, second segment of hind tarsus with three platellae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1401,1408,1751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
MALE GENITALIA. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[506,628,1408,1435]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5F–G</figureCitation>
) in ventral view symmetrical; in lateral view, lateral lobes arcuate and extended caudally. MediOventral prOcess lanceOlar in ventral view. Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1344,1443,1470]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5F, H</figureCitation>
) flat tubular, dorsal margin slightly convex, ventral margin curved, apical margin expanded downward in lateral view; 2.5× as long as wide in dorsal view; anal style strap-shaped, not extending beyond anal segment. Gonostyli (
<figureCitation box="[442,565,1549,1576]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5G, I</figureCitation>
) symmetrical ventrally; in inner lateral view, base of ventral margin concave, apical margin rounded. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[707,830,1584,1611]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1842,1868]" captionTargetBox="[231,1355,270,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-100@11.[227,1361,266,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862183/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5J–M</figureCitation>
) with four processes. 
<collectingRegion box="[1088,1166,1584,1610]" country="France" name="Centre" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Centre</collectingRegion>
of dorsal margin of periandrium with a short laminal process, base large, apex bifurcated, directed dorsocaudad; ventrally around midlength of periandrium with a slender spinose process, slightly curved, directed caudad. Endosoma large, basal part highly sclerotized, apical part with two processes bearing small teeth: one wide and flat, with its tip directed ventrad, the Other directed ventrOcephalad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[187,1400,1798,1966]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
FEMALE GENITALIA. Tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[554,714,1798,1824]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1434,1460]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,267,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-174@12.[183,1406,259,1393]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862187/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6A–B, D</figureCitation>
) moderately sclerotized, with a large,nearly elliptical wax plate. Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[442,534,1833,1859]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1434,1460]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,267,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-174@12.[183,1406,259,1393]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862187/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) rectangular, 1.9 × as long as wide in dorsal view, anal style linguiform. Gonapophysis VIII (
<figureCitation box="[436,526,1868,1894]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1434,1460]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,267,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-174@12.[183,1406,259,1393]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862187/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
) elongate, slightly curved upwards. Gonapophysis IX (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1279,1868,1894]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1434,1460]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,267,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-174@12.[183,1406,259,1393]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862187/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
) with one middle tooth, distance ratio between middle tooth to apex and length of denticulate portion 1.6. Gonoplac (
<figureCitation box="[196,288,1939,1965]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1434,1460]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,267,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-174@12.[183,1406,259,1393]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862187/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
) rod-like, 5.2 × as long as wide in lateral view. Posterior vagina pattern as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[1279,1372,1939,1965]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1434,1460]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,267,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-174@12.[183,1406,259,1393]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Andes furcutus Wang, Zhang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862187/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
